        "Description": "\"In the evening we happened, in our walk, to find the Erholung, where a concert was going forward. The walks in the garden are beautifully arched over with trees fir chiefly which with their falling leaves make a matting that deadens the sound of one's footsteps-a great charm to me. We sat down among the company, made up almost entirely of women, most of them good-looking well dressed bourgeoises, chatting with an air of real friendliness over their knitting etc. When we came home I read some of L.'s M.S. aloud.\" - George Eliot, Personal Diary (1854)",
